20for%20participating%20in%20a%20Ku%20Klux%20Klan%20march.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EMary%20Trump%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMary%20MacLeod%20Trump%20(1912-2000)%20was%20a%20Scottish%20immigrant%20born%20on%20the%20Isle%20of%20Lewis.%20She%20came%20to%20the%20US%20in%201930%20with%20just%20%2450%20and%20worked%20as%20a%20domestic%20house%20help%20before%20meeting%20Fred.%20The%20couple%20married%20in%201936%20and%20had%20five%20children%3A%20Maryanne%2C%20Fred%20Jr.%2C%20Elizabeth%2C%20Donald%2C%20and%20Robert.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDonald%20Trump's%20Siblings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaryanne%20Trump%20Barry%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20eldest%20sibling%2C%20Maryanne%20Trump%20Barry%20(1937-2023)%2C%20was%20a%20US%20federal%20judge%20who%20served%20for%20decades%2C%20including%20appointments%20under%20Presidents%20Reagan%20and%20Clinton.%20She%20was%20a%20critic%20of%20Donald%20Trump%20in%20private%20conversations%20revealed%20by%20her%20niece%2C%20Mary%20Trump.%20She%20had%20one%20son%2C%20David%20William%20Desmond.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EFred%20Trump%20Jr%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFred%20Jr.%20(1938-1981)%20was%20the%20eldest%20son%20and%20Fred%20Sr.'s%20initial%20choice%20to%20lead%20the%20family%20business.%20However%2C%20his%20struggles%20with%20alcoholism%20derailed%20his%20career.%20He%20worked%20as%20a%20pilot%20before%20dying%20of%20a%20heart%20attack%20at%2042.%20Fred%20Jr.%20had%20two%20children%2C%20Mary%20Trump%20and%20Fred%20Trump%20III.%20Mary%20later%20became%20a%20prominent%20critic%20of%20the%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EElizabeth%20Trump%20Grau%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%201942%2C%20Elizabeth%20worked%20at%20J.P.%20Morgan%20and%20remains%20one%20of%20the%20most%20private%20Trump%20siblings.%20Married%20to%20documentary%20producer%20James%20Grau%2C%20she%20lives%20in%20Palm%20Beach.%20They%20have%20no%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%