2Fus%2Fhow-can-we-stop-what-is-happening-lip-reader-decodes-bush-obama-conversation%2Famp_articleshow%2F117417927.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fhow-can-we-stop-what-is-happening-lip-reader-decodes-bush-obama-conversation%2Famp_articleshow%2F117417927.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20India-Bangladesh%20Friction%3A%20What%20You're%20Seeing%20Is%20Not%20Real%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERecent%20border%20tensions%20between%20India%20and%20Bangladesh%20have%20led%20to%20public%20tensions%2C%20even%20as%20the%20whole%20political%20situation%20resembles%20something%20close%20to%20a%20noodle%20soup.%20Bangladeshi%20government%20officials%E2%80%94or%20semi-government%2C%20in%20this%20case%E2%80%94say%20one%20thing%20and%20do%20another.%20Then%20there%20are%20the%20endless%20vitriolic%20statements%20from%20the%20so-called%20%E2%80%98student%20leaders'%2C%20who%20seem%20more%20intent%20on%20consolidating%20their%20power%20than%20getting%20to%20their%20stated%20goal%20of%20%E2%80%98real%20democracy'.%20One%20wonders%20what%20direction%20is%20being%20set%20by%20Chief%20Advisor%20Mohammad%20Yunus%2C%20the%20unelected%20%E2%80%98head'%20of%20the%20country%2C%20as%20he%20wades%20into%20the%20mess%2C%20together%20with%20his%20officials.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20border%20situation%20has%20calmed%20down%20marginally%2C%20though%20there%20are%20reports%20still%20of%20tensions%20at%20specific%20points%2C%20even%20as%20political%20barbs%20continue%20to%20be%20aimed%20from%20Dhaka.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Triggered%20Things%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20in%20the%20news%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Border%20Guards%20Bangladesh%20(BGB)%20stopped%20work%20at%20some%20six%20to%20seven%20points%20along%20the%20border%2C%20despite%20the%202015%20Land%20Boundary%20agreement%20and%20existing%20protocols%20for%20dealing%20with%20such%20disputes.%20The%20media%20picked%20up%20the%20news%20and%20ran%20with%20it%2C%20failing%20to%20mention%20that%20the%20whole%20situation%20had%20begun%20after%20the%20Border%20Security%20Force%20foiled%20smugglers%20from%20entering%20the%20area.%20The%20incident%20spiralled%20out%20of%20control%20as%20villagers%20on%20both%20sides%20stepped%20into%20the%20melee.%20The%20truth%20of%20the%20matter%20is%20that%20most%20parts%20of%20the%204%2C096-km%20border%2C%20particularly%20Malda%20district%2C%20where%20the%20clashes%20occurred%2C%20are%20known%20for%20smuggling%20of%20all%20kinds%2C%20particularly%20fake%20Indian%20currency%20supplied%20by%20racketeers%20along%20the%20Indo-Nepal%20border%2C%20phensedyl%2C%20a%20banned%20cough%20syrup%20used%20in%20place%20of%20alcohol%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20and%20cattle%2C%20a%20highly%20profitable%20racket%20for%20both%20sides.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20means%20that%20incidents%20of%20firing%20are%20common%20as%20border%20forces%20try%20to%20deal%20with%20a%20variety%20of%20crimes.%20Inevitably%2C%20that%20leads%20to%20incidents%20being%20blown%20out%20of%20proportion%20or%20taken%20out%20of%20context.%20In%20the%20present%20instance%2C%20a%20prominent%20Bangladeshi%20daily%20railed%20against%20India's%20%E2%80%9Cruthless%20border%20policy%E2%80%9D%20citing%20%E2%80%9Calleged%E2%80%9D%20deaths%2C%20without%20any%20attempt%20to%20verify%20what%20the%20incident%20had%20been%20all%20about.%20Another%20prominent%20source%20reported%20the%20death%20of%20a%20Bengali%20man%2C%20again%20%E2%80%9Callegedly%E2%80%9D%20beaten%20to%20death%20by%20the%20BSF%2C%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20vague%20statements%20from%20his%20widow.%20These%20comments%20are%20then%20multiplied%20poisonously%20on%20social%20media%2C%20on%20both%20sides.%20The%20simple%20fact%20is%20this%3A%20border%20criminals%20jeopardise%20the%20security%20of%20both%20countries.%20It%20is%20entirely%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20both%20India%20and%20Bangladesh%20to%20cooperate%20over%20this.%20Which%20is%20why%20the%20meeting%20of%20the%20border%20forces%E2%80%94postponed%20twice%20after%20the%20removal%20of%20the%20Hasina%20government%E2%80%94on%20January%2016%20at%20Benapole%20ended%20with%20public%20declarations%20of%20friendship%20and%20BGB%20officials%20calling%20it%20a%20%E2%80%98productive'%20session.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20%E2%80%98Official'%20Version%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20the%20official%20version.%20Home%20Adviser%20Lt.%20Gen.%20(Retd.)%20Md.%20Jahangir%20Alam%20Chowdhury%20declared%20the%20border%20%E2%80%9Calmost%20normal%E2%80%9D%20and%20stated%20that%20the%20construction%20of%20barbed%20wire%20fencing%20had%20already%20been%20stopped.%20That's%20not%20the%20reality%3B%20fencing%20has%20resumed%20peacefully%2C%20as%20per%20agreements.%20Chowdhury%2C%20who%20earlier%20headed%20BGB%20in%20what%20can%20only%20be%20described%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98difficult'%20period%2C%20also%20declared%20that%20his%20%E2%80%98government'%20had%20not%20been%20consulted%20before%20the%20BSF%20began%20its%20fencing%E2%80%94also%20far%20from%20the%20truth%E2%80%94and%20that%20the%20Indian%20High%20Commissioner%20had%20been%20%E2%80%98summoned'.%20Foreign%20Secretary%20Jashimuddin%20chose%20to%20go%20the%20same%20route%2C%20adding%2C%20significantly%2C%20that%20earlier%20border%20agreements%20made%20between%202010%20and%202023%20were%20%E2%80%9Cunequal%E2%80%9D.%20In%20short%2C%20agreements%20signed%20under%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20government%20are%20going%20to%20be%20questioned.%20India's%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20reacted%20by%20summoning%20the%20Bangladeshi%20High%20Commissioner%2C%20with%20its%20statement%20saying%20simply%20that%20all%20protocols%20and%20agreements%20had%20been%20adhered%20to.%20In%20sum%2C%20what%20was%20in%20essence%20a%20smuggling-induced%20incident%20of%20trivial%20proportions%20was%20turned%20into%20a%20major%20incident%20by%20political%20actors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMilitary%20Stays%20Aloof%E2%80%94Almost%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20military%20chose%20to%20remain%20aloof%20from%20these%20political%20shenanigans%2C%20with%20Army%20Chief%20Gen.%20Waker%20uz%20Zaman%20taking%20a%20realistic%20tone%20in%20an%20interview%2C%20observing%20that%20both%20India%20and%20Bangladesh%20need%20each%20other%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20will%20not%20do%20anything%20%E2%80%A6that%20goes%20against%20their%20strategic%20interests%E2%80%9D.%20He%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9C%20We%20will%20expect%20that%20our%20neighbour%20does%20nothing%20that%20is%20contrary%20to%20our%20interests%E2%80%9D%20referring%20also%20to%20the%20water-sharing%20issue.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmidst%20all%20this%2C%20a%20positive%20development%20went%20almost%20entirely%20unnoticed.%20An%20army%20delegation%20comprising%20both%20serving%20officers%20and%20retired%20officers%20attended%20the%20%E2%80%98Vijay%20Diwas'%20in%20Delhi%2C%20to%20the%20delight%20of%20veterans%20on%20this%20side%20as%20well.%20What%20did%20get%20coverage%20was%20an%20entirely%20unnecessary%20Twitter%20onslaught%20against%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi's%20congratulatory%20messages%20on%20the%201971%20victory%2C%20by%20student%20%E2%80%98advisors'%20Hasnat%20Abdullah%2C%20Asif%20Nazrul%20and%20Ishraque%20Hossain%20of%20the%20Bangladesh%20National%20Party%20(BNP).%20Most%20tellingly%2C%20Yunus%20chose%20to%20retweet%20one%20of%20these%20comments.%20Again%2C%20a%20dual%20position%2C%20with%20political%20actors%20weighing%20in%20to%20turn%20an%20entirely%20non-issue%20into%20a%20political%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20is%20also%20being%20made%20of%20a%20visit%20to%20Pakistan%20of%20an%20army%20delegation%20led%20by%20Lt-Gen%20S%20M%20Kamr-ul-Hassan%2C%20Principal%20Staff%20Officer%20(PSO)%20of%20the%20Armed%20Forces%20Division%20of%20Bangladesh.%20That's%20not%20an%20office%20with%20the%20highest%20military%20powers.%20What%20is%20worrying%2C%20however%2C%20is%20that%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%20the%20Liberation%2C%20the%20Pakistan%20army%20will%20return%20to%20Bangladesh%20to%20train%20senior%20army%20officers.%20In%20that%20same%20week%20came%20a%20decision%20to%20issue%20visas%20for%20Pakistanis%20without%20security%20clearance.%20This%20was%20done%20by%20the%20Home%20Ministry's%20Security%20Services%20Division.%20That%20would%20seem%20like%20another%20political%20dig%2C%20except%20that%20there%20are%20rumours%20of%20divisions%20within%20the%20army%2C%20which%20includes%20a%20faction%20led%20by%20a%20Lieutenant%20General%20earlier%20heading%20military%20intelligence%20and%20close%20to%20student%20leaders.%20This%20is%20not%20unlikely%20given%20Bangladesh's%20history%20of%20coups%20and%20counter%20coups.%20However%2C%20the%20point%20is%20that%20the%20Army%20Chief%20will%20have%20to%20maintain%20a%20careful%20balance%20in%20his%20position%20to%20avoid%20losing%20authority%2C%20particularly%20since%20he%20hasn't%20been%20in%20his%20post%20for%20too%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EStudents%20Have%20Lost%20The%20Plot%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20student%20leaders%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20who%20were%20once%20heading%20Bangladesh's%20%E2%80%98anti-discriminatory'%20movement%2C%20are%20now%20doing%20some%20discrimination%20of%20their%20own.%20Hasnat%20Abdullah%20recently%20threatened%20to%20%E2%80%98break%20the%20pens%E2%80%98%20of%20%E2%80%98fascists'%20arguing%20for%20allowing%20the%20Awami%20league%20to%20participate%20in%20elections.%20Another%20student%20%E2%80%98advisor'%2C%20Salahuddin%20Amar%2C%20refused%20to%20attend%20the%20commencement%20ceremony%20of%20a%20new%20batch%20of%20police%20officers%20citing%20political%20interference.%20Given%20the%20hatred%20against%20the%20police%2C%20this%20step%20is%20politically%20popular%2C%20though%20hardly%20realistic%20considering%20that%20these%20officers%20are%20from%20an%20entirely%20new%20batch.%20It%20seems%20Hasnat%20and%20his%20cronies%2C%20whose%20virulently%20anti-India%20position%20is%20now%20melded%20with%20hatred%20for%20Hasina%2C%20want%20to%20position%20themselves%20as%20candidates%20in%20future%20elections.%20Yunus%20seems%20to%20be%20in%20the%20same%20game%20as%20he%20dodges%20the%20question%20of%20announcing%20elections.%20The%20quietest%20of%20all%20is%20the%20Jamaat%20e%20Islami%2C%20whose%20members%20are%20everywhere%E2%80%94in%20the%20bureaucracy%2C%20the%20army%2C%20and%20almost%20every%20other%20institution.%20They%20may%20emerge%20as%20the%20hidden%20kingmakers.%20Every%20visiting%20foreign%20dignitary%2C%20including%20the%20European%20Union%20ambassador%2C%20calls%20on%20their%20headquarters.%20Once%20openly%20pro-Pakistan%20and%20anti-India%2C%20they%20are%20likely%20to%20follow%20a%20more%20cautious%20line%20now%20as%20they%20play%20the%20political%20chess%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESmoke%20And%20Mirrors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20announced%20that%20it%20will%20try%20to%20sort%20out%20a%20visa%20crisis%20as%20many%20centres%20have%20closed%20due%20to%20fears%20of%20violence.%20Over%201%2C500%20students%20are%20waiting%20for%20their%20visas%20even%20as%20the%20High%20Commission%20is%20processing%20emergency%20medical%20cases.%20Trade%20has%20resumed%20at%20its%20normal%20pace%20and%20various%20branches%20of%20the%20government%20are%20going%20about%20their%20bilateral%20business%2C%20despite%20reports%20of%20%E2%80%98scrutiny'%20of%20India-assisted%20projects.%20However%2C%20all%20this%20is%20political%20noise%3B%20nothing%20has%20been%20done%20yet.%20Expect%20more%20of%20the%20same%20till%20a%20government%20is%20not%20just%20elected%20but%20settles%20down%20to%20normal%20business.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20nothing%20at%20all%20has%20been%20said%20in%20public%20about%20the%20fact%20that%20about%2010%25%20of%20Bangladesh's%20total%20debt%20is%20owed%20to%20China.%20Foreign%20Advisor%20Touhid%20Hossain%20will%20soon%20be%20in%20Beijing%20with%20a%20request%20to%20extend%20repayments%20by%2030%20years%20and%20for%20budget%20support.%20In%20sum%2C%20the%20whole%20issue%20is%20like%20smoke%20and%20mirrors.%20What%20is%20seen%20in%20public%20is%20far%20from%20the%20reality.%20Delhi%20would%20be%20wise%20to%20wait%20it%20out%2C%20quietly.%20In%20the%20present%20storm%20of%20political%20verbal%20excess%2C%20the%20less%20said%2C%20the%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Tara%20Kartha%20is%20a%20former%20director%20of%20the%20National%20Security%20Council%20Secretariat)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737442020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fpagcgin_bsf-generic-border-security-force-ani_625x300_24_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findia-and-bangladesh-the-reality-is-not-what-it-seems-7523076%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20sum%2C%20the%20whole%20issue%20is%20like%20smoke%20and%20mirrors.%20What%20is%20seen%20in%20public%20is%20far%20from%20the%20reality.%20Delhi%20would%20be%20wise%20to%20wait%20it%20out%2C%20quietly.%20In%20the%20present%20storm%20of%20political%20verbal%20excess%2C%20the%20less%20said%2C%20the%20better.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findia-and-bangladesh-the-reality-is-not-what-it-seems-7523076%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Taliban%20announces%20US-Afghan%20prisoner%20exchange%20deal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737441905000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-117418324%2Cimgsize-864220.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fsouth-asia%2Ftaliban-announces-us-afghan-prisoner-exchange-deal%2Farticleshow%2F117418006.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3